{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"DE-RISK E3 (offline) CONFIRMS the S2 refactor: 11/45 prompts interpolate PER-RUN data into the SYSTEM body — completion_verifier/code_quality/security/tests/ticket_quality use {{ticket_context}}+{{ticket_id}}; plan_review_* use {{plan}}. Cross-run caching of these requires relocating per-run data to the USER message (or a stable-vs-volatile split). NOTE: the CONTAINER system prompt's {{plan}} is the PARENT plan, which is STABLE across the per-child fan-out — which is exactly why S1 caching works (E1). So S2's refactor targets the generic gate prompts, not the container."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782559856748240001,"uuid":"75c8b6b1-634d-4860-85b1-09e444bee671"}